<!-- Paste this entire section as your first message in a new AI thread -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

## Instructions for AI

When generating flowchart diagrams, apply the following visual theme exactly as specified. Do not invent new colors, do not add extra CSS overrides, and do not change the theme directive.

## Brand Guidance — AskJamie

Use this theme for:
- Support flows and helpdesk processes
- Step-by-step user guidance diagrams
- AI assistant conversation flows
- Explainer diagrams for non-technical users
- Onboarding and "how it works" content

Do NOT use this theme for:
- Deep technical architecture (use OverKill Hill P³ instead)
- Executive strategy decks

---

## Required: Theme directive

Choose ONE of the two formats below based on your renderer. Never use both in the same diagram.

### Format A — \`%%{init}%%\` directive (universal, Mermaid v9+)

> Use this for: Microsoft Loop, Notion, older renderers, or anywhere YAML frontmatter is not supported.

\`\`\`
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#fdfbf7", "primaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "primaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "lineColor": "#2d6f7e", "secondaryColor": "#f6f2ee", "secondaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "secondaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "tertiaryColor": "#e1ecef", "tertiaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "textColor": "#2e2b29", "background": "#f6f2ee", "mainBkg": "#fdfbf7", "nodeBorder": "#2d6f7e", "clusterBkg": "#e8f4f7", "titleColor": "#2d6f7e", "edgeLabelBackground": "#f6f2ee", "fontFamily": "Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
\`\`\`

### Format B — YAML frontmatter (preferred, Mermaid v10.5+)

> Use this for: Mermaid Live Editor, VS Code with Mermaid extension, GitHub (where supported). This format is the current Mermaid standard and deprecates \`%%{init}%%\`.

\`\`\`
---
# Mermaid v10.5+ preferred format — use instead of %%{init}%% where supported
config:
  theme: base
  themeVariables:
    primaryColor: "#fdfbf7"
    primaryTextColor: "#2e2b29"
    primaryBorderColor: "#2d6f7e"
    lineColor: "#2d6f7e"
    secondaryColor: "#f6f2ee"
    secondaryTextColor: "#2e2b29"
    secondaryBorderColor: "#2d6f7e"
    tertiaryColor: "#e1ecef"
    tertiaryTextColor: "#2e2b29"
    tertiaryBorderColor: "#2d6f7e"
    textColor: "#2e2b29"
    background: "#f6f2ee"
    mainBkg: "#fdfbf7"
    nodeBorder: "#2d6f7e"
    clusterBkg: "#e8f4f7"
    titleColor: "#2d6f7e"
    edgeLabelBackground: "#f6f2ee"
    fontFamily: "Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"
---
\`\`\`

---

## Required: Metadata comments

Add these comment lines immediately after the theme directive:

\`\`\`
%% Theme: AskJamie
%% Theme ID: askjamie
%% Tool: https://overkillhill.com/projects/mermaid-theme-builder/
\`\`\`

---

## Semantic classDef library

This is the complete styling vocabulary for this theme. Apply these classDef classes to nodes using \`:::className\` syntax. Do NOT add any other fill, stroke, or color values — use only these classes.

\`\`\`mermaid
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#fdfbf7", "primaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "primaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "lineColor": "#2d6f7e", "secondaryColor": "#f6f2ee", "secondaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "secondaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "tertiaryColor": "#e1ecef", "tertiaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "textColor": "#2e2b29", "background": "#f6f2ee", "mainBkg": "#fdfbf7", "nodeBorder": "#2d6f7e", "clusterBkg": "#e8f4f7", "titleColor": "#2d6f7e", "edgeLabelBackground": "#f6f2ee", "fontFamily": "Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
flowchart TD
    classDef primary fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29
    classDef secondary fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29
    classDef tertiary fill:#e1ecef,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29
    classDef platform fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29
    classDef boundary fill:#e8f4f7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-dasharray:5
    classDef actor fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29,font-weight:bold
    classDef gate fill:#2d6f7e,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#f6f2ee
    classDef control fill:#e1ecef,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29
    classDef log fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29,font-style:italic
    classDef question fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-dasharray:3
    classDef accent fill:#2d6f7e,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#f6f2ee
    classDef deepBlue fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29,stroke-width:2px
    classDef slate fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#fdfbf7
    classDef scope fill:#e8f4f7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-width:2px
    classDef outOfScope fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2e2b29,stroke-dasharray:8,opacity:0.6
    classDef redDash fill:#3b0e0e,stroke:#b91c1c,color:#fecaca,stroke-dasharray:4

    %% Usage example: NodeLabel:::primary
    %% Apply a class to a node: A[My Node]:::secondary
    %% Apply to a decision node: B{Choice}:::gate
\`\`\`

### Class reference table

| Class | Role | When to use |
|-------|------|-------------|
| \`primary\` | Main action / primary entity | Core nodes, key steps, subject of the diagram |
| \`secondary\` | Supporting / related entity | Adjacent systems, related processes |
| \`tertiary\` | Background / context | Passive nodes, reference items |
| \`platform\` | Platform / infrastructure | Hosting layer, operating environment |
| \`boundary\` | System boundary (dashed) | External system boundaries, context limits |
| \`actor\` | Person / user / role | Human actors, teams, personas |
| \`gate\` | Decision / gateway | Diamond decision nodes, routing logic |
| \`control\` | Control / management | Orchestrators, managers, approval nodes |
| \`log\` | Log / audit / record (italic) | Audit trails, event logs, history |
| \`question\` | Open question / TBD (dashed) | Unknowns, pending decisions, assumptions |
| \`accent\` | Highlighted / key result | Outcomes, final states, primary outputs |
| \`deepBlue\` | Deep emphasis / dark primary | Stressed primary nodes, thick border variant |
| \`slate\` | Neutral / muted | Low-priority nodes, supporting details |
| \`scope\` | In-scope boundary | Items explicitly in scope |
| \`outOfScope\` | Out-of-scope (faded, dashed) | Explicitly excluded items |
| \`redDash\` | Warning / error / blocker | Error states, blockers, known failures |

---

## Subgraph tier patterns

Use \`style SubgraphName ...\` statements to apply visual hierarchy to subgraphs. Replace \`SubgraphName\` with the actual subgraph ID.

\`\`\`mermaid
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#fdfbf7", "primaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "primaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "lineColor": "#2d6f7e", "secondaryColor": "#f6f2ee", "secondaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "secondaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "tertiaryColor": "#e1ecef", "tertiaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "textColor": "#2e2b29", "background": "#f6f2ee", "mainBkg": "#fdfbf7", "nodeBorder": "#2d6f7e", "clusterBkg": "#e8f4f7", "titleColor": "#2d6f7e", "edgeLabelBackground": "#f6f2ee", "fontFamily": "Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
flowchart TD
    %% Tier 1 — Primary system boundary (most prominent)
    style SubgraphName fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e

    %% Tier 2 — Secondary system or service grouping
    style SubgraphName fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e

    %% Tier 3 — Tertiary context or supporting group
    style SubgraphName fill:#e1ecef,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e

    %% Tier 4 — Cluster / infrastructure boundary
    style SubgraphName fill:#e8f4f7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-dasharray:5

    %% Tier 5 — Out-of-scope / external system
    style SubgraphName fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#fdfbf7,stroke-dasharray:8,opacity:0.7

    %% Tier 6 — Annotation / note boundary (no fill)
    style SubgraphName fill:transparent,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-dasharray:2
\`\`\`

---

## Theme: AskJamie

Calm mid-century tones with muted aquas and beige — clean, readable, ideal for guides and documentation

**Intended use:** Support flows, helpdesk diagrams, explainers, user-assistance workflows, and friendly AI-generated step-by-step guides

### Color reference
  - Primary (nodes): \`#fdfbf7\`
  - Primary text: \`#2e2b29\`
  - Primary border: \`#2d6f7e\`
  - Lines & arrows: \`#2d6f7e\`
  - Secondary nodes: \`#f6f2ee\`
  - Secondary text: \`#2e2b29\`
  - Secondary border: \`#2d6f7e\`
  - Tertiary nodes: \`#e1ecef\`
  - Tertiary text: \`#2e2b29\`
  - Tertiary border: \`#2d6f7e\`
  - Text color: \`#2e2b29\`
  - Background: \`#f6f2ee\`
  - Main background: \`#fdfbf7\`
  - Node border: \`#2d6f7e\`
  - Cluster background: \`#e8f4f7\`
  - Title color: \`#2d6f7e\`

### Font
\`Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif\`

---

## Rules

1. ALWAYS start the diagram with the theme directive (Format A or Format B above) — no exceptions.
2. Add the metadata comment block immediately after the theme directive.
3. Use \`flowchart TD\` as the diagram type unless the user specifies otherwise.
4. Keep node labels concise (under 60 characters each).
5. Style nodes using ONLY the classDef classes defined above — apply with \`:::className\` syntax.
6. Do NOT add inline \`fill:\`, \`stroke:\`, or \`color:\` values on individual nodes — use classDef classes instead.
7. Do NOT change any color values — reproduce them exactly as shown.
8. Use subgraph tier styles for visual hierarchy — never leave subgraphs unstyled.
9. If the diagram type changes, preserve the exact same theme directive.
10. If the diagram type does not support classDef (e.g. sequenceDiagram, erDiagram), omit classDef statements entirely — the theme directive handles all styling.

---

## Example output structure

\`\`\`mermaid
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#fdfbf7", "primaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "primaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "lineColor": "#2d6f7e", "secondaryColor": "#f6f2ee", "secondaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "secondaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "tertiaryColor": "#e1ecef", "tertiaryTextColor": "#2e2b29", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#2d6f7e", "textColor": "#2e2b29", "background": "#f6f2ee", "mainBkg": "#fdfbf7", "nodeBorder": "#2d6f7e", "clusterBkg": "#e8f4f7", "titleColor": "#2d6f7e", "edgeLabelBackground": "#f6f2ee", "fontFamily": "Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
%% Theme: AskJamie
%% Theme ID: askjamie
%% Tool: https://overkillhill.com/projects/mermaid-theme-builder/
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B[Process]
    B:::primary --> C{Decision}:::gate
    C -->|Yes| D[End]:::accent
    C -->|No| B
\`\`\`

---

