## Subgraph tier patterns

Use \`style SubgraphName ...\` statements to apply visual hierarchy to subgraphs. Replace \`SubgraphName\` with the actual subgraph ID.

\`\`\`mermaid
---
# Mermaid v10.5+ preferred format — use instead of %%{init}%% where supported
config:
  theme: base
  themeVariables:
    primaryColor: "#fdfbf7"
    primaryTextColor: "#2e2b29"
    primaryBorderColor: "#2d6f7e"
    lineColor: "#2d6f7e"
    secondaryColor: "#f6f2ee"
    secondaryTextColor: "#2e2b29"
    secondaryBorderColor: "#2d6f7e"
    tertiaryColor: "#e1ecef"
    tertiaryTextColor: "#2e2b29"
    tertiaryBorderColor: "#2d6f7e"
    textColor: "#2e2b29"
    background: "#f6f2ee"
    mainBkg: "#fdfbf7"
    nodeBorder: "#2d6f7e"
    clusterBkg: "#e8f4f7"
    titleColor: "#2d6f7e"
    edgeLabelBackground: "#f6f2ee"
    fontFamily: "Open Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"
---
flowchart TD
    %% Tier 1 — Primary system boundary (most prominent)
    style SubgraphName fill:#fdfbf7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e

    %% Tier 2 — Secondary system or service grouping
    style SubgraphName fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e

    %% Tier 3 — Tertiary context or supporting group
    style SubgraphName fill:#e1ecef,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e

    %% Tier 4 — Cluster / infrastructure boundary
    style SubgraphName fill:#e8f4f7,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-dasharray:5

    %% Tier 5 — Out-of-scope / external system
    style SubgraphName fill:#f6f2ee,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#fdfbf7,stroke-dasharray:8,opacity:0.7

    %% Tier 6 — Annotation / note boundary (no fill)
    style SubgraphName fill:transparent,stroke:#2d6f7e,color:#2d6f7e,stroke-dasharray:2
\`\`\`

