## Instructions for AI

When generating flowchart diagrams, apply the following visual theme exactly as specified. Do not invent new colors, do not add extra CSS overrides, and do not change the theme directive.

## Brand Guidance — OverKill Hill P³

Use this theme for:
- Technical architecture diagrams
- Systems design and infrastructure maps
- AI tooling and orchestration flows
- Strategy and executive-facing presentations
- Anything that needs to look precise, structured, and serious

Do NOT use this theme for:
- Consumer-facing or casual content
- Playful or lightweight explainers

---

## Required: Theme directive

Use the \`%%{init}%%\` directive (Format A) — compatible with Mermaid v9+, Microsoft Loop, Notion, and most renderers.

\`\`\`
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#111827", "primaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "primaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "lineColor": "#c46a2c", "secondaryColor": "#181f26", "secondaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "secondaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "tertiaryColor": "#1c3a34", "tertiaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "textColor": "#e5e7eb", "background": "#111827", "mainBkg": "#111827", "nodeBorder": "#c46a2c", "clusterBkg": "#0d1117", "titleColor": "#c46a2c", "edgeLabelBackground": "#181f26", "fontFamily": "DM Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
\`\`\`

---

## Required: Metadata comments

Add these comment lines immediately after the theme directive:

\`\`\`
%% Theme: OKHP3
%% Theme ID: overkill-hill
%% Tool: https://overkillhill.com/projects/mermaid-theme-builder/
\`\`\`

---

## Semantic classDef library

This is the complete styling vocabulary for this theme. Apply these classDef classes to nodes using \`:::className\` syntax. Do NOT add any other fill, stroke, or color values — use only these classes.

\`\`\`mermaid
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#111827", "primaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "primaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "lineColor": "#c46a2c", "secondaryColor": "#181f26", "secondaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "secondaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "tertiaryColor": "#1c3a34", "tertiaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "textColor": "#e5e7eb", "background": "#111827", "mainBkg": "#111827", "nodeBorder": "#c46a2c", "clusterBkg": "#0d1117", "titleColor": "#c46a2c", "edgeLabelBackground": "#181f26", "fontFamily": "DM Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
flowchart TD
    classDef primary fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb
    classDef secondary fill:#181f26,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb
    classDef tertiary fill:#1c3a34,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb
    classDef platform fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb
    classDef boundary fill:#0d1117,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c,stroke-dasharray:5
    classDef actor fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb,font-weight:bold
    classDef gate fill:#c46a2c,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#111827
    classDef control fill:#1c3a34,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb
    classDef log fill:#181f26,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb,font-style:italic
    classDef question fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c,stroke-dasharray:3
    classDef accent fill:#c46a2c,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#111827
    classDef deepBlue fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb,stroke-width:2px
    classDef slate fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#111827
    classDef scope fill:#0d1117,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c,stroke-width:2px
    classDef outOfScope fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#e5e7eb,stroke-dasharray:8,opacity:0.6
    classDef redDash fill:#3b0e0e,stroke:#b91c1c,color:#fecaca,stroke-dasharray:4

    %% Usage example: NodeLabel:::primary
    %% Apply a class to a node: A[My Node]:::secondary
    %% Apply to a decision node: B{Choice}:::gate
\`\`\`

### Class reference table

| Class | Role | When to use |
|-------|------|-------------|
| \`primary\` | Main action / primary entity | Core nodes, key steps, subject of the diagram |
| \`secondary\` | Supporting / related entity | Adjacent systems, related processes |
| \`tertiary\` | Background / context | Passive nodes, reference items |
| \`platform\` | Platform / infrastructure | Hosting layer, operating environment |
| \`boundary\` | System boundary (dashed) | External system boundaries, context limits |
| \`actor\` | Person / user / role | Human actors, teams, personas |
| \`gate\` | Decision / gateway | Diamond decision nodes, routing logic |
| \`control\` | Control / management | Orchestrators, managers, approval nodes |
| \`log\` | Log / audit / record (italic) | Audit trails, event logs, history |
| \`question\` | Open question / TBD (dashed) | Unknowns, pending decisions, assumptions |
| \`accent\` | Highlighted / key result | Outcomes, final states, primary outputs |
| \`deepBlue\` | Deep emphasis / dark primary | Stressed primary nodes, thick border variant |
| \`slate\` | Neutral / muted | Low-priority nodes, supporting details |
| \`scope\` | In-scope boundary | Items explicitly in scope |
| \`outOfScope\` | Out-of-scope (faded, dashed) | Explicitly excluded items |
| \`redDash\` | Warning / error / blocker | Error states, blockers, known failures |

---

## Subgraph tier patterns

Use \`style SubgraphName ...\` statements to apply visual hierarchy to subgraphs. Replace \`SubgraphName\` with the actual subgraph ID.

\`\`\`mermaid
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "themeVariables": {"primaryColor": "#111827", "primaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "primaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "lineColor": "#c46a2c", "secondaryColor": "#181f26", "secondaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "secondaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "tertiaryColor": "#1c3a34", "tertiaryTextColor": "#e5e7eb", "tertiaryBorderColor": "#c46a2c", "textColor": "#e5e7eb", "background": "#111827", "mainBkg": "#111827", "nodeBorder": "#c46a2c", "clusterBkg": "#0d1117", "titleColor": "#c46a2c", "edgeLabelBackground": "#181f26", "fontFamily": "DM Sans, system-ui, sans-serif"}}}%%
flowchart TD
    %% Tier 1 — Primary system boundary (most prominent)
    style SubgraphName fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c

    %% Tier 2 — Secondary system or service grouping
    style SubgraphName fill:#181f26,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c

    %% Tier 3 — Tertiary context or supporting group
    style SubgraphName fill:#1c3a34,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c

    %% Tier 4 — Cluster / infrastructure boundary
    style SubgraphName fill:#0d1117,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c,stroke-dasharray:5

    %% Tier 5 — Out-of-scope / external system
    style SubgraphName fill:#111827,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#111827,stroke-dasharray:8,opacity:0.7

    %% Tier 6 — Annotation / note boundary (no fill)
    style SubgraphName fill:transparent,stroke:#c46a2c,color:#c46a2c,stroke-dasharray:2
\`\`\`

